{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":760,"text":"Chris Anderson: So Robert\nspent the last few years"},{"time":3480,"text":"think about how weird human behavior is,"},{"time":5840,"text":"and how inadequate most\nof our language trying to explain it is."},{"time":10080,"text":"And it's very exciting to hear him\nexplain some of the thinking behind it"},{"time":14480,"text":"in public for the first time."},{"time":16160,"text":"Over to you now, Robert Sapolsky."}]},{"cues":[{"time":18280,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":23040,"text":"Robert Sapolsky: Thank you."},{"time":24680,"text":"The fantasy always runs\nsomething like this."},{"time":27960,"text":"I've overpowered his elite guard,"},{"time":30160,"text":"burst into his secret bunker"},{"time":32119,"text":"with my machine gun ready."},{"time":33960,"text":"He lunges for his Luger."},{"time":35880,"text":"I knock it out of his hand."},{"time":37720,"text":"He lunges for his cyanide pill."},{"time":40080,"text":"I knock that out of his hand."},{"time":41840,"text":"He snarls,"},{"time":43160,"text":"comes at me with otherworldly strength."},{"time":45400,"text":"We grapple, we fight,"},{"time":47120,"text":"I manage to pin him down"},{"time":49040,"text":"and put on handcuffs."},{"time":51480,"text":"\"Adolf Hitler,\" I say,"},{"time":53520,"text":"\"I arrest you for crimes\nagainst humanity.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":58000,"text":"Here's where the Medal of Honor\nversion of the fantasy ends"},{"time":61000,"text":"and the imagery darkens."},{"time":62880,"text":"What would I do if I had Hitler?"},{"time":65160,"text":"It's not hard to imagine\nonce I allow myself."},{"time":68720,"text":"Sever his spine at the neck."},{"time":70880,"text":"Take out his eyes with a blunt instrument."},{"time":73280,"text":"Puncture his eardrums. Cut out his tongue."},{"time":76080,"text":"Leave him alive on a respirator,"},{"time":78240,"text":"tube-fed, not able to speak\nor move or see or hear, just to feel,"},{"time":83560,"text":"and then inject him\nwith something cancerous"},{"time":86840,"text":"that's going to fester and pustulate"},{"time":89120,"text":"until every cell in his body\nis screaming in agony,"},{"time":93080,"text":"until every second\nfeels like an eternity in hell."},{"time":97680,"text":"That's what I would do to Hitler."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101920,"text":"I've had this fantasy since I was a kid,"},{"time":103960,"text":"still do sometimes,"},{"time":105480,"text":"and when I do, my heart speeds up --"},{"time":108160,"text":"all these plans for the most evil,\nwicked soul in history."},{"time":113840,"text":"But there's a problem,"},{"time":115120,"text":"which is I don't actually believe\nin souls or evil,"},{"time":118040,"text":"and I think wicked belongs in a musical."},{"time":120600,"text":"But there's some people\nI would like to see killed,"},{"time":123040,"text":"but I'm against the death penalty."},{"time":124880,"text":"But I like schlocky violent movies,"},{"time":127000,"text":"but I'm for strict gun control."},{"time":128800,"text":"But then there was a time\nI was at a laser tag place,"},{"time":131880,"text":"and I had such a good time\nhiding in a corner shooting at people."},{"time":136360,"text":"In other words, I'm your basic\nconfused human when it comes to violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141760,"text":"Now, as a species, we obviously\nhave problems with violence."},{"time":145120,"text":"We use shower heads to deliver poison gas,"},{"time":148200,"text":"letters with anthrax,\nairplanes as weapons,"},{"time":151320,"text":"mass rape as a military strategy."},{"time":153200,"text":"We're a miserably violent species."},{"time":155920,"text":"But there's a complication,"},{"time":157440,"text":"which is we don't hate violence,"},{"time":159840,"text":"we hate the wrong kind."},{"time":161720,"text":"And when it's the right kind,"},{"time":163200,"text":"we cheer it on, we hand out medals,"},{"time":165720,"text":"we vote for, we mate with\nour champions of it."},{"time":168880,"text":"When it's the right kind of violence,"},{"time":170720,"text":"we love it."},{"time":172520,"text":"And there's another complication,"},{"time":174200,"text":"which is, in addition to us\nbeing this miserably violent species,"},{"time":178280,"text":"we're also this extraordinarily\naltruistic, compassionate one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":183520,"text":"So how do you make sense\nof the biology of our best behaviors,"},{"time":186840,"text":"our worst ones and all of those\nambiguously in between?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":190880,"text":"Now, for starters,"},{"time":192160,"text":"what's totally boring is understanding\nthe motoric aspects of the behavior."},{"time":196480,"text":"Your brain tells your spine,\ntells your muscles"},{"time":199680,"text":"to do something or other,"},{"time":200960,"text":"and hooray, you've behaved."},{"time":202920,"text":"What's hard is understanding\nthe meaning of the behavior,"},{"time":206600,"text":"because in some settings,\npulling a trigger is an appalling act;"},{"time":210440,"text":"in others, it's heroically\nself-sacrificial."},{"time":213440,"text":"In some settings, putting your hand\none someone else's"},{"time":216400,"text":"is deeply compassionate."},{"time":217880,"text":"In others, it's a deep betrayal."},{"time":219800,"text":"The challenge is to understand"},{"time":221360,"text":"the biology of the context\nof our behaviors,"},{"time":224640,"text":"and that's real tough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227040,"text":"One thing that's clear, though,\nis you're not going to get anywhere"},{"time":230240,"text":"if you think there's going to be\nthe brain region or the hormone"},{"time":234680,"text":"or the gene or the childhood experience"},{"time":237440,"text":"or the evolutionary mechanism\nthat explains everything."},{"time":241040,"text":"Instead, every bit of behavior\nhas multiple levels of causality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":246800,"text":"Let's look at an example."},{"time":248840,"text":"You have a gun."},{"time":250720,"text":"There's a crisis going on:"},{"time":252320,"text":"rioting, violence, people running around."},{"time":254920,"text":"A stranger is running at you\nin an agitated state --"},{"time":258120,"text":"you can't quite tell if the expression\nis frightened, threatening, angry --"},{"time":263240,"text":"holding something\nthat kind of looks like a handgun."},{"time":266480,"text":"You're not sure."},{"time":267720,"text":"The stranger comes running at you"},{"time":269640,"text":"and you pull the trigger."},{"time":271400,"text":"And it turns out\nthat thing in this person's hand"},{"time":274360,"text":"was a cell phone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":276200,"text":"So we asked this biological question:"},{"time":278440,"text":"what was going on\nthat caused this behavior?"},{"time":281640,"text":"What caused this behavior?"},{"time":283560,"text":"And this is a multitude of questions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":285880,"text":"We start."},{"time":287120,"text":"What was going on in your brain\none second before you pulled that trigger?"},{"time":291560,"text":"And this brings us into the realm\nof a brain region called the amygdala."},{"time":295280,"text":"The amygdala, which is\ncentral to violence, central to fear,"},{"time":299240,"text":"initiates volleys of cascades"},{"time":301960,"text":"that produce pulling of a trigger."},{"time":304240,"text":"What was the level of activity\nin your amygdala one second before?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":308880,"text":"But to understand that,\nwe have to step back a little bit."},{"time":312280,"text":"What was going on in the environment\nseconds to minutes before"},{"time":315880,"text":"that impacted the amygdala?"},{"time":317640,"text":"Now, obviously, the sights,\nthe sounds of the rioting,"},{"time":320760,"text":"that was pertinent."},{"time":322000,"text":"But in addition,"},{"time":323240,"text":"you're more likely to mistake\na cell phone for a handgun"},{"time":326720,"text":"if that stranger was male"},{"time":329000,"text":"and large and of a different race."},{"time":332360,"text":"Furthermore, if you're in pain,"},{"time":334520,"text":"if you're hungry, if you're exhausted,"},{"time":336720,"text":"your frontal cortex\nis not going to work as well,"},{"time":339280,"text":"part of the brain whose job it is\nto get to the amygdala in time"},{"time":342960,"text":"saying, \"Are you really sure\nthat's a gun there?\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":346800,"text":"But we need to step further back."},{"time":348960,"text":"Now we have to look\nat hours to days before,"},{"time":352160,"text":"and with this, we have entered\nthe realm of hormones."},{"time":355160,"text":"For example, testosterone,"},{"time":357320,"text":"where regardless of your sex,"},{"time":359080,"text":"if you have elevated\ntestosterone levels in your blood,"},{"time":361960,"text":"you're more likely to think\na face with a neutral expression"},{"time":365360,"text":"is instead looking threatening."},{"time":367440,"text":"Elevated testosterone levels,\nelevated levels of stress hormones,"},{"time":371320,"text":"and your amygdala\nis going to be more active"},{"time":373640,"text":"and your frontal cortex\nwill be more sluggish."}]},{"cues":[{"time":377200,"text":"Pushing back further,\nweeks to months before,"},{"time":380080,"text":"where's the relevance there?"},{"time":381560,"text":"This is the realm of neural plasticity,"},{"time":384120,"text":"the fact that your brain\ncan change in response to experience,"},{"time":388080,"text":"and if your previous months\nhave been filled with stress and trauma,"},{"time":392280,"text":"your amygdala will have enlarged."},{"time":394160,"text":"The neurons will have become\nmore excitable,"},{"time":396400,"text":"your frontal cortex would have atrophied,"},{"time":398760,"text":"all relevant to what happens\nin that one second."}]},{"cues":[{"time":402320,"text":"But we push back even more, back years,"},{"time":405000,"text":"back, for example, to your adolescence."},{"time":407520,"text":"Now, the central fact\nof the adolescent brain"},{"time":410040,"text":"is all of it is going full blast"},{"time":412800,"text":"except the frontal cortex,"},{"time":414520,"text":"which is still half-baked."},{"time":416280,"text":"It doesn't fully mature\nuntil you're around 25."},{"time":419480,"text":"And thus, adolescence and early adulthood"},{"time":422720,"text":"are the years where environment\nand experience sculpt your frontal cortex"},{"time":427880,"text":"into the version you're going to have\nas an adult in that critical moment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":432800,"text":"But pushing back even further,"},{"time":434600,"text":"even further back\nto childhood and fetal life"},{"time":438080,"text":"and all the different versions\nthat that could come in."},{"time":440920,"text":"Now, obviously, that's the time\nthat your brain is being constructed,"},{"time":444200,"text":"and that's important,"},{"time":445440,"text":"but in addition,\nexperience during those times"},{"time":448760,"text":"produce what are called\nepigenetic changes,"},{"time":451760,"text":"permanent, in some cases,"},{"time":453440,"text":"permanently activating\ncertain genes, turning off others."},{"time":457800,"text":"And as an example of this,"},{"time":459320,"text":"if as a fetus you were exposed to a lot\nof stress hormones through your mother,"},{"time":464360,"text":"epigenetics is going to produce\nyour amygdala in adulthood"},{"time":467800,"text":"as a more excitable form,"},{"time":469760,"text":"and you're going to have\nelevated stress hormone levels."}]},{"cues":[{"time":472960,"text":"But pushing even further back,"},{"time":474880,"text":"back to when you were just a fetus,"},{"time":476600,"text":"back to when all you were\nwas a collection of genes."},{"time":479440,"text":"Now, genes are really\nimportant to all of this,"},{"time":481840,"text":"but critically, genes don't\ndetermine anything,"},{"time":484600,"text":"because genes work differently\nin different environments."},{"time":488640,"text":"Key example here:"},{"time":489920,"text":"there's a variant of a gene called MAO-A,"},{"time":493080,"text":"and if you have that variant,"},{"time":494760,"text":"you are far more likely\nto commit antisocial violence"},{"time":499440,"text":"if, and only if,\nyou were abused as a child."},{"time":503440,"text":"Genes and environment interact,"},{"time":505840,"text":"and what's happening in that one second\nbefore you pull that trigger"},{"time":509480,"text":"reflects your lifetime\nof those gene-environment interactions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514679,"text":"Now, remarkably enough,\nwe've got to push even further back now,"},{"time":518320,"text":"back centuries."},{"time":519720,"text":"What were your ancestors up to."},{"time":522080,"text":"And if, for example,\nthey were nomadic pastoralists,"},{"time":525280,"text":"they were pastoralists,"},{"time":526560,"text":"people living in deserts or grasslands"},{"time":529160,"text":"with their herds of camels, cows, goats,"},{"time":531840,"text":"odds are they would have invented\nwhat's called a culture of honor"},{"time":535920,"text":"filled with warrior classes,"},{"time":538160,"text":"retributive violence, clan vendettas,"},{"time":540880,"text":"and amazingly, centuries later,"},{"time":543160,"text":"that would still be influencing\nthe values with which you were raised."}]},{"cues":[{"time":547800,"text":"But we've got to push even further back,"},{"time":549960,"text":"back millions of years,"},{"time":551720,"text":"because if we're talking about genes,"},{"time":553800,"text":"implicitly we're now talking\nabout the evolution of genes."},{"time":557480,"text":"And what you see is, for example,"},{"time":559720,"text":"patterns across different primate species."},{"time":562240,"text":"Some of them have evolved\nfor extremely low levels of aggression,"},{"time":566680,"text":"others have evolved\nin the opposite direction,"},{"time":569240,"text":"and floating there in between\nby every measure are humans,"},{"time":573160,"text":"once again this confused,\nbarely defined species"},{"time":577080,"text":"that has all these potentials\nto go one way or the other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":581560,"text":"So what has this gotten us to?"},{"time":583400,"text":"Basically, what we're seeing here is,"},{"time":585400,"text":"if you want to understand a behavior,"},{"time":587320,"text":"whether it's an appalling one,\na wondrous one,"},{"time":590200,"text":"or confusedly in between,"},{"time":591960,"text":"if you want to understand that,"},{"time":593520,"text":"you've got take into account\nwhat happened a second before"},{"time":597000,"text":"to a million years before,"},{"time":598480,"text":"everything in between."}]},{"cues":[{"time":600160,"text":"So what can we conclude at this point?"},{"time":602160,"text":"Officially, it's complicated."},{"time":604480,"text":"Wow, that's really helpful."},{"time":606120,"text":"It's complicated,"},{"time":607400,"text":"and you'd better be\nreal careful, real cautious"},{"time":611000,"text":"before you conclude\nyou know what causes a behavior,"},{"time":614360,"text":"especially if it's a behavior\nyou're judging harshly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":618600,"text":"Now, to me, the single most important\npoint about all of this"},{"time":622600,"text":"is one having to do with change."},{"time":625000,"text":"Every bit of biology I have mentioned here\ncan change in different circumstances."},{"time":631400,"text":"For example, ecosystems change."},{"time":634240,"text":"Thousands of years ago,\nthe Sahara was a lush grassland."},{"time":638680,"text":"Cultures change."},{"time":640320,"text":"In the 17th century, the most terrifying\npeople in Europe were the Swedes,"},{"time":644680,"text":"rampaging all over the place."},{"time":646440,"text":"This is what the Swedish\nmilitary does now."},{"time":648640,"text":"They haven't had a war in 200 years."},{"time":651280,"text":"Most importantly,"},{"time":652760,"text":"brains change."},{"time":654400,"text":"Neurons grow new processes."},{"time":656440,"text":"Circuits disconnect."},{"time":657920,"text":"Everything in the brain changes,"},{"time":659600,"text":"and out of this come extraordinary\nexamples of human change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":665400,"text":"First one:"},{"time":667040,"text":"this is a man named John Newton,"},{"time":668760,"text":"a British theologian"},{"time":670120,"text":"who played a central role in the abolition\nof slavery from the British Empire"},{"time":674880,"text":"in the early 1800s."},{"time":676920,"text":"And amazingly, this man\nspent decades as a younger man"},{"time":681680,"text":"as the captain of a slave ship,"},{"time":683840,"text":"and then as an investor in slavery,"},{"time":686800,"text":"growing rich from this."},{"time":688960,"text":"And then something changed."},{"time":691640,"text":"Something changed in him,"},{"time":693200,"text":"something that Newton himself celebrated\nin the thing that he's most famous for,"},{"time":698480,"text":"a hymn that he wrote:"},{"time":700120,"text":"\"Amazing Grace.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":703040,"text":"This is a man named Zenji Abe\non the morning of December 6, 1941,"},{"time":707960,"text":"about to lead a squadron of Japanese\nbombers to attack Pearl Harbor."},{"time":712960,"text":"And this is the same man\n50 years later to the day"},{"time":716520,"text":"hugging a man who survived\nthe attack on the ground."},{"time":720120,"text":"And as an old man,"},{"time":721560,"text":"Zenji Abe came to a collection\nof Pearl Harbor survivors"},{"time":726000,"text":"at a ceremony there"},{"time":727440,"text":"and in halting English apologized\nfor what he had done as a young man."}]},{"cues":[{"time":732760,"text":"Now, it doesn't always require decades."},{"time":734680,"text":"Sometimes, extraordinary change\ncould happen in just hours."},{"time":738400,"text":"Consider the World War I\nChristmas truce of 1914."},{"time":742800,"text":"The powers that be\nhad negotiated a brief truce"},{"time":745960,"text":"so that soldiers could go out,"},{"time":747600,"text":"collect bodies from no-man's-land\nin between the trench lines."},{"time":751520,"text":"And soon British and German soldiers"},{"time":754480,"text":"were doing that,"},{"time":755960,"text":"and then helping each other carry bodies,"},{"time":758440,"text":"and then helping each other\ndig graves in the frozen ground,"},{"time":762120,"text":"and then praying together,"},{"time":763400,"text":"and then having Christmas together\nand exchanging gifts,"},{"time":766240,"text":"and by the next day,\nthey were playing soccer together"},{"time":769480,"text":"and exchanging addresses\nso they could meet after the war."},{"time":772880,"text":"That truce kept going\nuntil the officers had to arrive"},{"time":776880,"text":"and said, \"We will shoot you"},{"time":778400,"text":"unless you go back\nto trying to kill each other.\""},{"time":780920,"text":"And all it took here was hours"},{"time":783080,"text":"for these men to develop\na completely new category of \"us,\""},{"time":787440,"text":"all of us in the trenches here"},{"time":789360,"text":"on both sides, dying for no damn reason,"},{"time":792160,"text":"and who is a \"them,\"\nthose faceless powers behind the lines"},{"time":795840,"text":"who were using them as pawns."}]},{"cues":[{"time":798680,"text":"And sometimes,\nchange can occur in seconds."},{"time":802720,"text":"Probably the most horrifying event\nin the Vietnam War"},{"time":806080,"text":"was the My Lai Massacre."},{"time":808000,"text":"A brigade of American soldiers"},{"time":810040,"text":"went into an undefended\nvillage full of civilians"},{"time":813080,"text":"and killed between 350 and 500 of them,"},{"time":816640,"text":"mass-raped women and children,"},{"time":819520,"text":"mutilated bodies."},{"time":821120,"text":"It was appalling."},{"time":822360,"text":"It was appalling because it occurred,\nbecause the government denied it,"},{"time":826640,"text":"because the US government eventually\ndid nothing more than a slap on the wrist,"},{"time":831040,"text":"and appalling because it almost certainly\nwas not a singular event."},{"time":835320,"text":"This man, Hugh Thompson, this is the man\nwho stopped the My Lai Massacre."},{"time":840440,"text":"He was piloting a helicopter gunship,"},{"time":843080,"text":"landed there, got out"},{"time":844920,"text":"and saw American soldiers shooting babies,"},{"time":848000,"text":"shooting old women,"},{"time":849400,"text":"figured out what was going on,"},{"time":851320,"text":"and he then took his helicopter"},{"time":853440,"text":"and did something that undid\nhis lifetime of conditioning"},{"time":857440,"text":"as to who is an \"us\" and who is a \"them.\""},{"time":859520,"text":"He landed his helicopter"},{"time":861400,"text":"in between some surviving villagers\nand American soldiers"},{"time":865040,"text":"and he trained his machine guns\non his fellow Americans,"},{"time":868720,"text":"and said, \"If you don't stop the killing,\nI will mow you down.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":874560,"text":"Now, these people\nare no more special than any of us."},{"time":877560,"text":"Same neurons, same neurochemicals,"},{"time":880160,"text":"same biology."},{"time":882400,"text":"What we're left with here\nis this inevitable cliche:"},{"time":885800,"text":"\"Those who don't study history\nare destined to repeat it.\""},{"time":888560,"text":"What we have here is the opposite of it."},{"time":890760,"text":"Those who don't study the history\nof extraordinary human change,"},{"time":895040,"text":"those who don't study the biology\nof what can transform us"},{"time":898600,"text":"from our worst to our best behaviors,"},{"time":901120,"text":"those who don't do this\nare destined not to be able"},{"time":904200,"text":"to repeat these incandescent,\nmagnificent moments."}]},{"cues":[{"time":908480,"text":"So thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":910040,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":920040,"text":"CA: Talks that really give you\na new mental model about something,"},{"time":923560,"text":"those are some of my favorite TED Talks,"},{"time":925520,"text":"and we just got one."},{"time":927960,"text":"Robert, thank you so much for that.\nGood luck with the book."},{"time":930840,"text":"That was amazing,"},{"time":932120,"text":"and we're going to try and get you\nto come here in person one year."},{"time":935320,"text":"Thank you so much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":936560,"text":"RS: Thank you. Thank you all."}]}]}